author: COMSOL
description: Ultra-High Molecular Weight Polyethylene (UHMWPE) is a material commonly employed in knee and hip joint replacements. The “small punch test” is designed to assess mechanical properties using very small samples, such that because of their size they can directly be explanted. This example demonstrates the use of the Bergstrom–Bischoff material model in the Polymer Viscoplasticity feature available in the Nonlinear Structural Materials Module.
